cs.CL, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.PL

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it discusses the use of finite-state transducers in language processing tasks such as part-of-speech tagging and speech recognition. It may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it discusses parallel processing on GPUs and optimization techniques for achieving better performance. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) because it deals with finite-state algorithms, and cs.PL (Programming Languages) because it discusses the implementation of FST composition on GPUs.
